By Ahmed Ubandoma First Lady Aisha Buhari, on Monday commiserated with the family of former Minister of Women Affairs, late Sen. Aisha Jummai Alhassan popularly called “Mama Taraba”. The first lady was accompanied to the deceased residence by her Special Assistant on African First Lady’s Peace Mission, Dr Mairo Almakura and other associates in Abuja. Buhari described late Alhassan as a courageous woman who stood for the advancement of women, especially the welfare and wellbeing of women and girl-child. She prayed to almighty Allah to grant the deceased eternal rest and give the family the fortitude to bear the loss. She also said the deceased was a source of inspiration, a detribalised woman and a pillar of support to all Nigerian women. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the late Alhassan died on May 7, after a protracted illness in a Cairo Hospital, Egypt. Alhassan served as Minister of Women Affairs under President Muhammadu Buhari’s administration from 2015 to 2018. (NAN) Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Like this:Like Loading... Like Loading...  	Related